The paper discusses a protocol for automatic filter propagation to mitigate DoS attacks, which is related to network security (cs.NI) and cybercrime (cs.CR). The proposed system also involves the use of routers and network resources, which falls under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the efficiency of the system in the face of continued Internet growth, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SE).
